==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stola
<hw>Sto"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Stolae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See <er>Stole</er> a
garment.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A long garment, descending
to the ankles, worn by Roman women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>stola</qex> was not allowed to be worn by courtesans, or
by women who had been divorced from their husbands.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairholt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stole</ent>⟦br⟧
